<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by Daanya on 04-10-2002 04:22 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">First level:
1000 damage (not 2000) over 24 seconds
2.5 cast time
24 second fear

Second level:
5000 damage over 24 seconds
5.0 cast time
24 second fear

Third level:
10000 damage over 24 seconds
7.5 cast time
24 second fear

Which, of course, doesn't make it particularly useful unfortunately as the best you could do would be level 3 in grey at level 59 (having BAotR). Get up jboots / run 3 and pull as many Shissars / skeles as you can. Take the next 2 minutes trying to get them all near each other then stand back and wait for them to come in.

Lose probably at least a bub of health when they reach you, take a step forward to be in the thick of them. Cast Stun Command and pray none resist.

You have 9 seconds so start Turn Undead and it should land about a second before stun wears off.

So every 72 minutes you can kill probably 10 or so (more is begging for the 1 resist it takes to interrupt TU and cause you to die waiting for SC to refresh).

Or, you can make a paladin, get Slay 3. Return to Grey and several times during the previous 72 minutes land a crit for just about as much as they have health (Snakes have bout 5k hp).

Run 3, Wisdom 3-5, SCM 3, MC 3, MGB. That's the maximum a cleric will ever need. The rest is complete fluff. It's why I did make a paladin and he will be getting Slay someday. Only 7 levels away until I go 100% AA exp  :)</TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
